class Solution:
    def alphabetBoardPath(self, target: str) -> str:
        i = j = 0
        ans = []
        for c in target:
            v = ord(c) - ord("a")
            x, y = v // 5, v % 5
            # Move left first to avoid going out of bounds when moving down to 'z'
            while j > y:
                j -= 1
                ans.append("L")
            while i > x:
                i -= 1
                ans.append("U")
            while j < y:
                j += 1
                ans.append("R")
            while i < x:
                i += 1
                ans.append("D")
            ans.append("!")
        return "".join(ans)
```

This solution correctly handles the movement on the alphabet board, including the special case for the letter 'z' which is at the bottom-left corner. The approach ensures that we move left and up before moving right and down to prevent invalid moves when reaching 'z'.
